text: Ypsolopha pseudoparallela is a moth of the family Ypsolophidae. It is known from Honshu island in Japan. The length of the forewings is 8.8-10.1 mm. ==Etymology== The specific name is a combination of the Greek pseudes (meaning false) and the specific name of the superficially similar species Ypsolopha parallela. ==References== Category:Ypsolophidae Category:Moths of Japan
title: Ypsolopha pseudoparallela
